text: Johannes Jacobus van Gastel (5 January 1887 - 5 March 1969) was an archer from the Netherlands. Van Gastel competed at the 1920 Summer Olympics.Jo van Gastel, Jr. == References == Category:1887 births Category:1969 deaths Category:Dutch archers Category:Olympic gold medalists for the Netherlands Category:Sportspeople from North Brabant Category:People from Tilburg
